x4freetext: High Flux Beam Reactor
Riso bent-crystal spectrometer.
Thermal neutron spectrum
Riso bent crystal spectrometer with
resolution of 400 eV at 1 MeV.
GeLi. detectors of 40 cm3. Typical energy
resolution is 2.5 keV FWHM for the 60Co lines.
At Riso: 37 mg of HgS with 97 % of 199Hg
At BNL: 70 mg HgO with 97 % of 199Hg.
For the bent-crystal spectrometer, the intensities
were corrected for the reflectivity of the crystal,
absorption between source and detector, self-
absorption in the gamma-ray source, and detector
efficiency.
For the GeLi, peak intensities were corrected for
detector efficiency and absorption and normalized
to the relative intensities of the bent-crystal
spectrometer measurements.
For the GeLi, energy calibration was made by
comparison with bent-crystal spectrometer energies
for some of the strongest lines between 1 and 2 MeV.
